The result of the visit was the decision to create an engineering center on the basis of the flagship of the domestic mechanical engineering industry. On September 4, 1986, the Government of the country decided to create an industry scientific and technical center (NTC) at the automobile plant. In 1987-1994, its main facilities were put into operation: an engineering building, design center, a complex for preparing vehicles for testing, a complex for studying electromagnetic compatibility, noise and vibrations, an aeroclimatic complex, buildings for experimental industrial and experimental production. In 1996, a full-scale wind tunnel was put into operation at the STC. V. V. Kadannikov (in 1986-1988).